barbara cook ( born october 25 , 1927 ) is an american singer and actress who first came to prominence in the 1950s after starring in the original broadway musicals plain and fancy ( 1955 ) , candide ( 1956 ) and the music man ( 1957 ) among others , winning a tony award for the last .

musicals : barbara cook won a tony for playing marian the librarian in the original production of this musical

the music man